"{\"uid\": \"today.com-news-paris-olympics-aya-nakamura-french-singer-rcna163920\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A Michael Kors Bag, Suede Slippers and More Holiday Gifts at Walmart - Starting at $9    Joyann Jeffrey  Trending News Reporter  Aya Nakamura gave a grand performance at the2024 Paris Olympicsopening ceremony when she performed two of her hit songs, \\\"Pookie\\\" and\\\"Djadja\\\" as well as Charles Aznavour's \\\"For Me Formidable.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Kors\", \"score\": 0.9999648004392552, \"rank\": 3.5200799913905854e-05, \"text\": \"Michael Kors\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Kors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Kors\"}, {\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On stage, Nakamura dazzled the crowd in agold Dior ensemblethat was covered in feathers.\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 369, \"end\": 373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dior\", \"score\": 0.9928088073444381, \"rank\": 0.007243280480827312, \"text\": \"Dior\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dior\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dior\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French president Emmanuel Macron toldThe Guardianwhy Nakamura was the perfect person to take the stage that night along with other performers such asC\\u00e9line Dion and Lady Gaga.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, \\\"She speaks to a good number of our fellow citizens, and I think she is absolutely in her rightful place in an opening or closing ceremony.\\\"\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read on to learn all about Aya Nakamura.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to herIMDb profile, Nakamura's real name is Aya Danioko and she was born on May 10, 1995, in Bamako, Mali, making her a Taurus.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 837, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_of_Yop_City\", \"score\": 0.9999996749243638, \"rank\": 3.250745655863919e-07, \"text\": \"Aya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_of_Yop_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_of_Yop_City\"}, {\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bamako\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.489190376401957e-28, \"text\": \"Bamako\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bamako\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bamako\"}, {\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9999982160209125, \"rank\": 1.7835435720187061e-06, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The New York Timesreports that she got her stage name from a character in \\\"Heroes,\\\" a science fiction series that aired on NBC between 2006 and 2010.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999998890416, \"rank\": 1.1099654573060152e-10, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999997461214074, \"rank\": 2.491033423466886e-07, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the show, there was a character called Hiro Nakamura, who had time travel and teleportation skills.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hiro_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hiro Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hiro_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hiro_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a little girl, Nakamura was raised in the suburbs of Paris and she is the eldest of five siblings.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997812665, \"rank\": 2.1857961054892003e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a 2017 interview withLe Monde, she shared that she was the one in her family that took singing seriously.\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone sings in my family.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am the only one who dared to sing 'for real,'\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to her label,Warner Music Group, Nakamura sold more than one million copies of her 2018 self-titled album, \\\"Nakamura,\\\" worldwide and has had her songs streamed more than four billion times on Spotify, making her album the most popular French-language album of all time on the platform.\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Music_Group\", \"score\": 0.9138532299718849, \"rank\": 0.0918677017187301, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Music_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Music_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spotify\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In her music, Nakamura likes to use a combination of French lyrics mixed with Arabic, English and West African languages like Bambara, the Malian language of her parents, perThe New York Times.\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1833, \"end\": 1839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999785074746356, \"rank\": 2.149167156386379e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Languages_of_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.82424150022929e-29, \"text\": \"West African languages\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Languages_of_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Languages_of_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bambara_language\", \"score\": 0.999576261762105, \"rank\": 0.00042391786707322735, \"text\": \"Bambara\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bambara_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bambara_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999998890416, \"rank\": 1.1099654573060152e-10, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In doing so, she creates music that is very diverse.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of her most popular songs on Spotify are \\\"Copiness\\\" and \\\"Djadja,\\\" which are featured on her sophomore album \\\"Nakamura.\\\"\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2062, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spotify\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\"}, {\"begin\": 2090, \"end\": 2096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\", \"score\": 0.5934202699024623, \"rank\": 0.5000000000001412, \"text\": \"Djadja\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Djadja_(song)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura is a proud mom.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although she rarely posts pictures of her child(ren) online, Nakamura spoke toVogue Franceabout what it's like to be a mother.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the interview, she confirmed she has a daughter and said she used to act just like her when she was a child.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I never took singing lessons.\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was like my daughter, singing in front of videos with a hairbrush as a microphone!\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Probably because I was imitating the songs I watched on TV.\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought it was great,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According toLe Monde, Nakamura\\u00a0began studying fashion at La Courneuve after she graduated from high school.\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2689, \"end\": 2701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Courneuve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.699787739238053e-24, \"text\": \"La Courneuve\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Courneuve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Courneuve\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was studying fashion at La Courneuve.\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2768, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Courneuve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.699787739238053e-24, \"text\": \"La Courneuve\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Courneuve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Courneuve\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to be a designer, but I stopped enjoying it, so I sang,\\\" she told the outlet.\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura also spoke more about it in an interview withVogue France.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999991122094192, \"rank\": 8.859324563859487e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said, \\\"When I was younger, I studied pattern making and I really wanted to be a pattern maker.\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It takes so much patience, though, and that's not my forte.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I quit in spite of myself simply because I could not.\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was my closest relationship with fashion.\\\"\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura understands that she's become an empowering role model for women.\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At the beginning of my career, I was rather skeptical about this idea of \\u200b\\u200ba role model.\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is a reality: I have influence,\\\" she toldCB News.\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If I allow, through my work and my commitments, certain women to assert themselves, then it is a source of pride!\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I believe that influence must be useful.\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Otherwise it is useless.\\\"\", \"from\": 3580, \"to\": 3605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked about her commitments, she said she's really taken a liking to women's emancipation.\", \"from\": 3607, \"to\": 3702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Women's emancipation.\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's my fight,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's all violence against women that I fight.\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If I can use my music and my fame for them, I never hesitate,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Joyann Jeffrey is a trending news reporter based in New York City  \\u00a9\\u00a02025 NBCUniversal Media, LLCApple\\u00ae, Apple logo\\u00ae and App Store\\u00ae are registered trademarks of Apple Inc.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 4049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3885, \"end\": 3892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinus_jeffreyi\", \"score\": 0.5623991977602881, \"rank\": 0.6648944910857081, \"text\": \"Jeffrey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinus_jeffreyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinus_jeffreyi\"}, {\"begin\": 3930, \"end\": 3943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.073895043499633e-15, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 3983, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999975414569444, \"rank\": 2.4582821077506095e-06, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 3999, \"end\": 4008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/App_store\", \"score\": 0.9999998295165969, \"rank\": 1.704835932793619e-07, \"text\": \"App Store\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/App_store\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/App_store\"}, {\"begin\": 4039, \"end\": 4049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2054025228879292e-31, \"text\": \"Apple Inc.\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}]}"